outputs.output_descr:
The African Mutual Accountability (MA) programme aims at building effective aid and development cooperation on the African Continent. This will be translated into a mutual accountability assessment questionnaire with indicators and methodology to strengthen capacities for mutual accountability in Africa. The expected outcomes of the programme are as follows:
1.	An in depth understanding and pan-African agreement on what mutual accountability at the country level requires in Africa and how improved accountability can increase effectiveness of development cooperation, strengthen African ownership of development processes and contribute to higher levels of human development;
2.	Capacities developed for mutual accountability in Africa, supporting countries to reach the agreed standards;
3.	International Advocacy on what mutual accountability entails in Africa and what African countries need from their international partners in this regard.
